          relating the <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">first</NUMEX>- and <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">second</NUMEX>-position <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">GC</ENAMEX> content to the
          <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">third</NUMEX>-position <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">GC</ENAMEX> content. However, if the frequencies of
          the <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">four</NUMEX> nucleotides at each codon position can vary
          independently with <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">GC</ENAMEX> content (subject to the constraint
          that the nucleotide frequencies at each position are
          constrained by a sum), it is necessary to characterize
          the regression lines of each <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">base</ENAMEX> at each position to
          make predictions about the nucleotide composition of the
          set of constant <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">bases</ENAMEX> at each position, and of the most
          likely <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">states</ENAMEX> of variable <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">bases</ENAMEX> for <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">a given</TIMEX> GC
          content.
