          positions × <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">2</NUMEX> parameters for each regression line) where,
          for each position, we plotted the percentage of each of
          the <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">four</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">bases</ENAMEX> against total <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">GC</ENAMEX> content. For a given
          total <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">GC</ENAMEX> content, the expected frequency of a particular
          base at a particular position is estimated directly from
          its regression line, which is based on <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">two</NUMEX> parameters
          (the slope and the intercept). This takes into account
          the fact that an <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">organism</ENAMEX> at a given <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">GC</ENAMEX> content will
